description:
&lt;p&gt;This is an opportunity for you to join a busy and varied IT Projects Team which implements primarily SystmOne projects across TSDFT’s Community and parts of Devon. We require a dynamic, pragmatic project manager, who is happy to communicate and influence staff at all levels, is organised and used to using PRINCE2.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will project manage the successful implementation of the TPP SystmOne maternity solution. You will need to show leadership, deal with conflicting priorities across the project lifecycle and have a track record of managing complex projects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of the NHS and SystmOne would be an advantage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You must be able to travel and work flexibly if required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a challenging role, but a rewarding one, where you will work as part of a modern, dynamic and supportive team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Initially a 10-month fixed term contract or secondment opportunity in line with project implementation timelines, but has the possibility of being extended/made permanent.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal discussion please contact Tracy Moss, Head of Strategic Systems’ Software Development, on 01803 653552.&lt;/p&gt;
